    "@id": "https://anchorfact.org/fact/fact-computer-science-001",
    "text": "Cron is a time-based job scheduler in Unix-like systems. `crontab -e` edits user jobs. Format: `minute hour day month weekday command`. Example: `0 2 * * * /backup.sh` runs daily at 2 AM. Cron is ideal for periodic maintenance: backups, log rotation, report generation.",
